fx losses on non-uk mortgage for uk property - tax deductable? fx losses on non-uk mortgage for uk property - tax deductable? foreign exchange (fx) losses on non-uk mortgages used to purchase uk property can be a complex topic for tax purposes. generally, if you have a mortgage denominated in a foreign currency (such as euros or dollars) to buy a uk property, any fx gains or losses arise when you convert the foreign currency back into pounds sterling, either for repayments or refinancing.

for uk tax purposes, whether fx losses are deductible depends on the nature of the letting or property business:

